div.p:
And Bleſſed is the fruit of thy wombe, Ieſus. This laſt word explicateth the whole ſentence: for this Bleſſed fruit of her wombe,
was nothing elſe but ſwet Ieſus;
• nd this fruit grew vpon no other • eethen vpon the B Virgin from whom we receaue this pleaſant & vitall fruite. In this Virgin (a Paradiſe of pleaſure) theſe ſpiritual fruits abound; for cōtayning this one fruit, which hath the nature of heauenly Manna, ſhe ſatisfieth the taſt of all ſpirituall ſoules; for Ieſus is a fruit contayning in it ſelfe all delightes.
